b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe38208.htm)  [Next](sbe38210.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1417930330/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Vedanta Sutras of Badarayana, Commentary by Sankara (SBE38)_ , tr. by\nGeorge Thibaut [1896] at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n66\\. And because (scripture) shows it.\n\nScripture moreover shows that the meditations do not go together, viz. in the\nfollowing passage, 'A Brahman priest who knows this saves the sacrifice, the\nsacrificer, and all the priests' ( _Kh_. Up. IV, 17, 10). For if all\nmeditations were to be combined, all priests would know them all, and the text\ncould not specially announce that the Brahman priest possessing a certain\nknowledge thereby saves the others.--The meditations may therefore, according\nto one's liking, be either combined or optionally employed.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 4, 1](sbe38210.htm)\n\n"